This paper discusses the principles and efficiency of planning algorithms, which are commonly studied in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and programming languages (cs.PL). The analysis also involves comparing two specific planners, which could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) or robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper emphasizes the importance of understanding underlying assumptions for constructing efficient planners, which could be relevant to software engineering (cs.SE).
